children.text: The labels to comply with AS2047 for the window and door frames installed throughout this dwelling do not appear to be installed, indicating that these frames do not comply with Australian Standards.

Under Part 3.0, Section 3.6.0 of Volume 2 of the National Construction Code's BCA (Building Code of Australia), performance requirements (P2.1 and P2.2.2) are satisfied if windows are designed and constructed in accordance with AS 2047, Windows and External Glazed Doors.
Section 8.2 - Labelling of AS 2047 requires the following;

The builder will need to provide evidence from the manufacturer to confirm that these window and door frames comply with the Australian Standards, by means of a formal test certificate that complies with Australian Standard AS2047. The building surveyor (who issues the building permit) should be immediately notified of this issue by the owner/purchaser, so they can assist by forcing the builder to comply with the requirements of the BCA and AS2047.
